  "prompt": "What did George Lucas think of the Force Awakens?",
  "response": "George Lucas, the creator of the *Star Wars* franchise, had mixed feelings about *The Force Awakens* (2015), directed by J.J. Abrams. While Lucas has praised the technical execution and the talent involved in the film, he also expressed some disappointment regarding its creative direction.\n\nIn interviews, Lucas indicated that he felt *The Force Awakens* relied too heavily on nostalgia and rehashed elements from the original trilogy, particularly *A New Hope*, rather than taking the story in a more innovative direction. He described his vision for the sequel trilogy as being more experimental and focused on \"going off into a new world,\" but he felt that Disney\u2019s approach was more about appealing to familiar themes and characters.\n\nLucas has made it clear that he holds no ill will toward the filmmakers or Disney, acknowledging that they were entitled to take the franchise in their own direction after selling the rights. However, his comments suggest a degree of creative disconnect between his original vision for the saga and the direction taken in *The Force Awakens* and the subsequent films.",
